This paper discusses the nonmonotonicity of logics for Artificial Intelligence, which is a key topic in the field of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the concept of formulae that respect monotonicity and are conservative, which are related to the study of logic (cs.LO) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also mentions theorem provers, which are related to cryptography and security (cs.CR) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
